                    <history>

                        <origin>
                            <origPlace cert="medium">Several marginalia on the flyleaves and later
                                folios mention events which took place "Dārende ḳażāsında Ḥacī
                                Dervīş maḥallesinde" (دارنده قضاسنده حاجی درویش محله‌سنده) i.e. in
                                the Hacıderviş neighbourhood of the town of Darende in present day
                                Malatya, Turkey, though it is unclear if the manuscript also
                                originated there.</origPlace>
                            <origDate when="1812-12-24" calendar="#Gregorian">Per the colophon, the
                                manuscript was completed on 12 Kānūn-i s̠ānī (1)226, i.e. 12 January
                                1812</origDate>
                        </origin>

                        <provenance> Per marginalia on <locus from="102b" to="102b">folio
                                102b</locus>, this manuscript appears to have spent some time in the
                            possession of one <persName key="" role="scr"><persName>Ocaḳcızāde ʿAlī
                                    Efendi Maḫdūmī</persName>
                                <persName>اوجاقجی زاده علی افندی مخدومی</persName></persName> of the
                            Hacıderviş neighbourhood of the town of Darende in present day Malatya,
                            Turkey. </provenance>

                        <acquisition> Purchased from <persName key="person_f4232"
                                >Thornton's</persName>, <date when="1974-01" calendar="#Gregorian"
                                >January 1974</date>. Sold erroneously as "Kurdish religious poems". </acquisition>


                    </history>

